 Smart Parsing Logic
The parser is designed to handle real-world, inconsistently formatted files:

Auto-detects column headers — recognizes variations like CGPA, SGPA, GPA, CPI, Marks, Percentage, etc.
Roll number detection — finds roll/hall ticket/enrollment/USN/PRN columns automatically
Backlog counting — counts subjects with a grade of 0 from grade columns in PDFs; reads explicit backlog columns from spreadsheets
Active vs. total backlogs — distinguishes cleared vs. pending backlog subjects
Branch / Section / Semester extraction — pulled from column data or PDF metadata headers
Delimiter auto-detection — handles comma, semicolon, and tab-separated files


